---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Learn who we are, how we test products, and the editorial standards behind every ReviewHive recommendation."
>
  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">

        <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-zinc-50 mb-6">About ReviewHive</h1>

        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none
          prose-headings:text-zinc-50
          prose-headings:font-bold
          prose-p:text-zinc-300
          prose-p:leading-relaxed
          prose-a:text-amber-400
          prose-a:no-underline
          hover:prose-a:underline
          prose-strong:text-zinc-200
          prose-li:text-zinc-300
          prose-hr:border-zinc-800">

          <p class="text-xl text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
            ReviewHive is an independent product review site dedicated to honest, useful recommendations — no hype, no paid placements, no fluff.
          </p>

          <h2>What We Do</h2>
          <p>
            We research, test, and review consumer products across tech, gear, home, and lifestyle. Every recommendation starts with hands-on time with the product, followed by weeks of real-world use. We aim to answer the question every shopper asks: <strong>"Is this actually worth buying?"</strong>
          </p>

          <h2>Our Editorial Standards</h2>
          <p>
            Our reviews are written based on independent testing and research. We do not accept payment for positive reviews or rankings. Brands may send us products to review, but this does not influence our opinions — and we'll tell you when that's the case.
          </p>
          <p>
            We use a consistent evaluation methodology for each product category, testing against a defined set of criteria rather than impressions alone.
          </p>

          <h2>Affiliate Links</h2>
          <p>
            ReviewHive participates in affiliate programs, including the Amazon Associates Program. This means we may earn a small commission when you buy through our links — at <strong>no additional cost to you</strong>. These commissions help keep the site running and allow us to keep testing new products.
          </p>
          <p>
            Affiliate relationships never influence our recommendations. If a product isn't worth buying, we'll say so. For the full details, see our <a href="/disclosure">Affiliate Disclosure</a>.
          </p>

          <h2>How We Test</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Research phase:</strong> We study spec sheets, user reviews, and existing coverage to understand what matters most in each category.</li>
            <li><strong>Hands-on testing:</strong> We purchase or obtain review units and use them in real daily scenarios.</li>
            <li><strong>Comparison:</strong> We test against competing products at the same price point wherever possible.</li>
            <li><strong>Long-term use:</strong> We note whether first impressions hold up over weeks of actual use.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
          <p>
            Have a product you think we should review? Found an error in one of our articles? Reach out at <a href="mailto:hello@yoursite.com">hello@yoursite.com</a>.
          </p>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
